A trainee lawyer from Siberia has won the title of the longest legs in Russia with her incredible gazelle-like 106cm pins.

Anastasia Strashevskaya, 18, from Novosibirsk, has been voted 'Miss Longest Legs' in a Russian national beauty contest.

Miss Strashevskaya won a £1,600 prize after beating 52 other contestants to win the title in the competition which also included categories Miss Bikini, Miss Sport, Miss Smile, and Miss Blonde.

